    "body": "@karalabe Yes. I got it. \r\nBtw, when the validator reached a block, it will commit propose (get from proposals variable of this node) to the chain, right? \r\nEx with 5 address: (address 1,2,...5) with address 1,2,3 is a validator, and follow these steps:\r\n- address 1,2,3 vote address 4 -> validators (it means they call propose API with auth: true)\r\n- address 2,3,4 vote address 4  from validator -> none (it means auth: false). \r\nAfter that, address 4 isn't a validator. But in the chain, we have a proposed vote address 4 -> validators (it is committed by address 1 ). Do you think this is a problem? ",
